It made no sense to pick investment X, so I was very confident that the leader picked investment Y. There was a small chance that the leader decided to be generous, but it was very unlikely, as the leader would have to act against their own interests.    If the maximum payoff for investment X exceeded the minimum payoff for investment Y, then there was a slightly greater chance of the leader picking X. The leader may see some individual benefit from picking investment X but it was still very unlikely.
